news.title: Manesar: Rampura Chowk-Naurangpur stretch to get 110 LED streetlights
news.para: The Municipal Corporation of Manesar (MCM) has awarded the contract for installing the lights to a private agency at a sanctioned cost of Rs 96 lakh. Currently, the contractor is installing the poles, and the entire project will take a maximum of three months.

news.title: Gross NPAs rise 3.3% for housing finance companies in December: CRISIL
news.para: On their part, housing finance companies are trying to change borrower behaviour and reduce additional slippages into GNPAs. This, however, will lead to increased operational intensity as they beef up their collection efforts.

news.title: Now, development charges in Haryana linked to collector rate
news.para: In a move that will impact a large part of population living under the jurisdiction of civic bodies of Haryana, the state’s urban local bodies department has linked the development charges to the collector’s rate of the area concerned.

news.title: Delhi court issues show cause notice to police on misleading statement regarding Sushil Ansal
news.para: ​The court issued the notice to the investigating officer (IO) of the case on an application moved by the complainant, alleging that the Lieutenant Governor of Delhi had already accorded the requisite sanction on September 16 last year, which was duly communicated to the DCP headquarters on the same day.

news.title: Chandigarh administration seeks progress report on land pooling policy
news.para: The draft is being prepared by Bengaluru-based Indian Institute of Human Settlement (IIHS). Recently, the administration had asked the IIHS to submit a revised draft policy on village development, regularisation of illegal structures and extension of lal dora.

news.title: Chandigarh: Criminal proceedings against floor-wise registration advertisement
news.para: Last year in November, the HC suggested, “The Administration to initiate necessary steps to criminally prosecute in accordance with law such persons who may misrepresent through any medium as regards sale of floor/storey/specific portion of a site/building.”

news.title: Government may soon carry out audit of EWS flats built in outer Delhi a decade ago
news.para: A team of Delhi State Industrial and Infrastructure Development Corporation (DSIIDC) engineers, which investigated the reasons behind the collapse of a block of flats in northwest Delhi’s Bawana earlier this month, found the condition of the buildings “highly dilapidated”, said sources.

news.title: Planet Smart City plans to raise 60 million euros to expand business in India, other countries
news.para: "The 60m capital increase is aimed at accelerating the implementation of Planet's ambitious business plan that includes the launch of approximately 54 smart projects over the next three years (a total of over 40,000 housing units)," the statement said.

news.title: Supertech twin towers: Demolition squad lands first blows in countdown to fall
news.para: Pre-demolition work is on in full swing at Ground Zero, the compound of Apex and Ceyane in Sector 93A, where a blast perimeter will be created to absorb shock and debris from the implosions that will flatten the 32-storey buildings, likely in the third week of May.

news.title: LIC wants to remain IDBI Bank shareholder for bancassurance benefits
news.para: With regard to the housing finance business, he said LIC Housing Finance can source business from IDBI Bank. Both cannot do as LIC is promoter of IDBI Bank and LIC Housing Finance, LIC Chairman M R Kumar said.

news.title: Give us flats nearby, say NBCC Green View residents
news.para: Currently, there are 35 families living in the highrise buildings of Green View and 90 families in the EWS flats, which are in the same compound. Of these, about 10 families living in the highrises have opted for rental accommodation and agreed to shift in seven days.

news.title: Gurugram: Amrapali homebuyers feel NBCC Green View tremors
news.para: The company, however, assured a bench of Justices U U Lalit and Bela M Trivedi that the PSU was committed to maintaining quality of construction and the controversy surrounding the Gurugram project should not be linked with Amrapali projects.

news.title: Provided information sought by Enforcement Directorate: Indiabulls Housing
news.para: The company said the ECIR (Enforcement Case Information Report) registered by ED stems out of an FIR filed by one Ashutosh Kamble, who is part of a long-running extortion and blackmail racket against the firm.

news.title: China's Zhenro Properties slumps after debt warning
news.para: Zhenro said in a filing late on Friday that its internal funds available for debt servicing have become increasingly limited since the announcement it made on Jan 4 about the redemption, citing adverse market conditions.

news.title: Rents reach 'insane' levels across US with no end in sight
news.para: In the 50 largest U.S. metro areas, median rent rose an astounding 19.3% from December 2020 to December 2021, according to a Realtor.com analysis of properties with two or fewer bedrooms.
